   "source": [
    "2) What is the difference between EBS and Instance Store, and how do you explain it?\n",
    "\n",
    "Ans:\n",
    "The difference between EBS and Instance Store are:\n",
    "    i) Elastic Block Store or EBS provides block level storage volume for Elastic Compute Cloud (EC2) instance and is independent of the life of the instance. The storage volume is exposed when linked to an EC2 instance. \n",
    "    Whereas, Instsance Store also provides block level storage for EC2 but for \"temporary\" period. It is located at disk which are physically attached to host computer.\n",
    "    \n",
    "    ii) EBS volume behaves like raw, unformatted block devices which is ideal to store long-term data. It is well suited for file systems, databases, or for any applications that require fine granular updates and access to raw, unformatted, block-level storage like database applications etc.\n",
    "    Whereas Instance store volume is ideal to store temporary information that changes frequently like buffers, caches and other temporary content etc.\n",
    "    \n",
    "    iii) EBS volume can detached from an EC2 instance and then attached to another EC2 instance and information is still available and used.\n",
    "    Whereas Instance volume loses the information that moment EC2 instance stops or terminates.\n",
    "    \n",
    "    iv) Additional EBS volume can be attached any time to an EC2 instance i.e. during launch and even during running.\n",
    "    Whereas, additional Instance volume can be attached only during launch of EC2 instance and not during running.\n",
    "    "
   ]
  },
