    "3) What are the different types of load balancers available in AWS?\n",
    "\n",
    "Ans:\n",
    "Amazon Elastic Load Balancer (EBS) is a managed load balancer that maintain traffic automatically between EC2 instances, containers or IP address available in one or more Availability zones.\n",
    "\n",
    "AWS offers 3 types of Load Balancer:\n",
    "\n",
    "i) Application Load Balancer - It is used to route http\\https or Layer 7 traffic. The routing decision is taken at application layer i.e. at http\\https header request and it supports dynamic host port mapping because of which, it allows to have multiple tasks from a single service on same container instance.\n",
    "\n",
    "ii) Network Load Balancer - It is used to route TCP or Layer 4 traffic i.e. it makes routing decision at transport layer (TCP\\SSL). It select the target using \"Flow hash routing\" algorithm and attempts to open a TCP connection to the selected target on the port specified in the listener configuration. It also support dynamic host port mapping.\n",
    "\n",
    "iii) Classic Load Balancer - It is used to route either at hhtp\\https (Layer 7) or at TCP (Layer 4) traffic. It is a connection-based balancer where requests are forwarded by the load balancer without looking-into any of these requests. They just get forwarded to the backend section.\n"
   ]
  },
