    "4) How does AWS IAM make a profit?\n",
    "\n",
    "Ans:\n",
    "AWS Identity and Access Management (IAM) are offerred at free of usage. However, user/account/organization are charged for using other AWS service using IAM.\n",
    "The services that are chargeable using IAM are:\n",
    "i) AWS CloudTrail - It is an AWS service that logs AWS account activity and API usage for auditing, monitoring and compliance.\n",
    "ii) AWS Cloud Directory - AWS Cloud Directory help to organize directory objects like users into multiple hierarchies to support many organizational pivots and relationshiop across directory information.\n",
    "iii) Amazon Cognito - It is a simple user identity and data synchronization service that helps you securely manage and synchronize app data for your users across their mobile devices.\n",
    "iv) AWS Control Tower - This AWS service helps to set up and govern a secure multiple AWS account called landing zones in case of very large organisation.\n",
    "\n",
    "Moreover, there is a service quotas for number of free users, groups, roles, policy etc. In order to increase them, reach out to support team who will increase with some charges applied.\n",
    "\n",
    "Further, IAM is only a service for user or its management. Due to its high security, availability, flexiblility and many other features, other services of AWS like EC2, S3 etc. are used in large areas and domain and AWS charges for the use of these services.\n",
    "\n",
    "This is how, IAM makes profit."
   ]
