    "5) Demonstrate the DynamoDB support mechanism.\n",
    "\n",
    "Ans:\n",
    "DynamoDb is a NoSQL database service which provides fast performance for the application and has the ability scale up and down automaticatlly. It is AWS managed i.e. users don’t have to worry about setup and configuration, hardware provisions, replication, throughput capacity planning, cluster scaling or software patching.\n",
    "\n",
    "The data stored DynamoDb is secured with encryption and provides reliability with service level agreement. It also back-up data automatically for safety and high availability. The in-memmory cache feature reduces the response time to microsecond from millisecond and thus provides high performance.\n",
    "\n",
    "It supports key-value data structure model and data is indexed using a primary key that is composed of partitiion key and secret key.\n",
    "\n",
    "It supports GET/PUT operations by using a user-defined primary key. It provides flexible querying by letting you query on non-primary vital attributes using global secondary indexes and local secondary indexes.\n",
    "\n",
    "It also supports conditional operation using boolean function, comparison operator and logical operator.\n",
    "\n",
    "It supports quick in-place atomic updates, where the numeric attribute’s increment and decrement can be done in arrow using just one API call or similarly, you can add or remove sets, lists, or maps.\n",
    "\n"
   ]
